# hub/.gcloudignore (mission-50 T3 — closes bug-36; task-386 extension)
#
# `gcloud builds submit` reads `.gcloudignore` if present, else falls back to
# `.gitignore`. `hub/.gitignore` excludes the staged tarballs
# (`apnex-storage-provider-*.tgz`, `apnex-repo-event-bridge-*.tgz` —
# intentional, to prevent accidental commits of the transient tarballs
# staged by `scripts/local/build-hub.sh`). Without this `.gcloudignore`,
# those exclusions propagate to the Cloud Build upload context and the
# Dockerfile `COPY apnex-<pkg>-*.tgz` steps fail because the tarballs are
# missing.
#
# This file is self-contained (does NOT use `#!include:.gitignore`). We mirror
# the meaningful excludes here, then re-include the staged tarballs.
#
# TODO(idea-186): when npm workspaces lands, this file + the hub/.gitignore
# tarball exclusions + the build-hub.sh transient-swap mechanic + the
# Dockerfile COPY lines all become obsolete. Sunset together — see
# `deploy/README.md` §"Cloud Build tarball staging (mission-50)" for the full
# cleanup list.

node_modules/

# Re-include the sovereign-package tarballs staged by scripts/local/build-hub.sh.
# (The leading `!` is documentation-style here — with self-contained
# .gcloudignore there's no prior exclusion to override — but it makes intent
# explicit and stays correct if a broader exclude is added above.)
!apnex-storage-provider-*.tgz
!apnex-repo-event-bridge-*.tgz
